navmid.graph
Class ListenerAssociationNode

java.lang.Object
  navmid.graph.Node
      navmid.graph.ListenerAssociationNode

public class ListenerAssociationNode
extends Node

A listener association node is a graph node created between a screen node and a class implementing the event listener functionality (which may be used for several screen nodes). The role is represented by a CallbackNode.Event.

Method Detail

link

public static void link(Node src,
                        Node dst,
                        CallbackNode.Event e)
Creates a callback binding between a Displayable and a listener with a given role. This means that events belonging to the role occuring on this displayable (or start stop nodes) will be treated by this listener.

Parameters:
src - the displayable abstract node that receives events,
dst - the listener abstract node that treats events,
e - the category of events treated.
